FBIS4-7801 "dreeu066_s_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-066 Daily Report 5 Apr 1994 SLOVENIA People's Party Demands Kucan's Resignation People's Party Demands Kucan's Resignation AU0504155994 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 1330 GMT 5 Apr 94 AU0504155994 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network Slovene BFN [Text] A public statement issued by the Slovene People's Party demands a debate on the responsibility of the state president [Milan Kucan] for the situation in Slovenia and his withdrawal, a State Chamber vote of no-confidence in the government, and early parliamentary and presidential elections. They demand this because of impossible conditions in the country due to an ever-increasing disaster among the Slovene people and the alienation of the authorities.
